[
    {
        "text": "Guys!",
        "start": 0.9,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you speak English good?",
        "start": 2.22,
        "duration": 3.9
    },
    {
        "text": "Or maybe you speak good English.",
        "start": 6.12,
        "duration": 3.55
    },
    {
        "text": "Or maybe you speak English well.",
        "start": 9.67,
        "duration": 3.47
    },
    {
        "text": "One of those sentences is wrong.",
        "start": 13.14,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "I sure hope you know which one.",
        "start": 15.54,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "But if you don't",
        "start": 17.76,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "or get confused like many students \nand native speakers.",
        "start": 18.94,
        "duration": 4.38
    },
    {
        "text": "keep watching.",
        "start": 23.54,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "Hello, guys.",
        "start": 27.9,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "My name is Fanny.",
        "start": 29.08,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "And in this video,\nI'm gonna tell you about a very common English",
        "start": 30.3,
        "duration": 4.2
    },
    {
        "text": "mistake\nthat many students make even native speakers.",
        "start": 34.5,
        "duration": 4.48
    },
    {
        "text": "Mostly when speaking English.",
        "start": 38.98,
        "duration": 1.919
    },
    {
        "text": "It's the difference between the words 'good'\nand 'well'.",
        "start": 40.899,
        "duration": 5.031
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you know the difference between the two\nwords?",
        "start": 45.93,
        "duration": 2.69
    },
    {
        "text": "It's not so much a writing mistake.",
        "start": 48.62,
        "duration": 3.3
    },
    {
        "text": "It's more of a speaking mistake.",
        "start": 51.92,
        "duration": 1.729
    },
    {
        "text": "Especially, in familiar contexts,\nbut you need to know about it and to fix it,",
        "start": 53.649,
        "duration": 6.75
    },
    {
        "text": "if you want to show off and speak good English.",
        "start": 60.399,
        "duration": 4.101
    },
    {
        "text": "So let's get started with a few examples.",
        "start": 64.5,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "‘He is a good tennis player.’",
        "start": 67.52,
        "duration": 4.4
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you think that sentence is right?",
        "start": 71.92,
        "duration": 2.98
    },
    {
        "text": "It is right.",
        "start": 74.9,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Why?",
        "start": 76.88,
        "duration": 1.18
    },
    {
        "text": "Because we have the adjective ‘good’\nand then the noun ‘tennis player’.",
        "start": 78.06,
        "duration": 4.8
    },
    {
        "text": "An adjective, as you know, describes a noun.",
        "start": 82.86,
        "duration": 4.99
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay so how is the tennis player?",
        "start": 87.85,
        "duration": 3.62
    },
    {
        "text": "The tennis player is good.",
        "start": 91.47,
        "duration": 2.48
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 93.95,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "When you say,\n‘You speak good English’",
        "start": 95.12,
        "duration": 3.09
    },
    {
        "text": "That's also a correct sentence.",
        "start": 98.21,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "You have a noun – ‘English’.",
        "start": 100.74,
        "duration": 1.94
    },
    {
        "text": "And an adjective describing that noun – ‘good’.",
        "start": 102.68,
        "duration": 4.36
    },
    {
        "text": "So how is your English?",
        "start": 107.04,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "It's good.",
        "start": 108.58,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "Third sentence is also a correct sentence.",
        "start": 109.58,
        "duration": 3.28
    },
    {
        "text": "‘Your English is good’.",
        "start": 112.86,
        "duration": 1.75
    },
    {
        "text": "As I've just said,\nan adjective that describes a noun.",
        "start": 114.61,
        "duration": 5.43
    },
    {
        "text": "Now if we say,\n‘This tennis player plays well’.",
        "start": 120.04,
        "duration": 3.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Is this correct?",
        "start": 124.0,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "It is correct\nbecause in this case,",
        "start": 126.56,
        "duration": 3.25
    },
    {
        "text": "you have no adjectives,\nbut you have an adverb.",
        "start": 129.81,
        "duration": 4.05
    },
    {
        "text": "Now an adverb describes a verb,\nanother adverb, or an adjective.",
        "start": 133.86,
        "duration": 7.12
    },
    {
        "text": "In this sentence, it describes the verb 'plays'.",
        "start": 140.98,
        "duration": 4.28
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, how do you play?",
        "start": 145.26,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "You play well.",
        "start": 147.79,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "So 'well' is an adverb.",
        "start": 149.33,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "‘You speak English well’ is also correct.",
        "start": 151.94,
        "duration": 4.42
    },
    {
        "text": "The adverb, ‘well’, describes the verb\n'to speak'.",
        "start": 156.36,
        "duration": 4.79
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay so there is a difference.",
        "start": 161.15,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "The adjective is good.",
        "start": 163.04,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "The adverb is well.",
        "start": 165.01,
        "duration": 3.46
    },
    {
        "text": "So when you say,\n‘You play good’,",
        "start": 168.47,
        "duration": 4.85
    },
    {
        "text": "do you think that's right?",
        "start": 173.32,
        "duration": 2.46
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't.",
        "start": 175.78,
        "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
        "text": "It's incorrect and you will hear many native\nspeakers tell you that.",
        "start": 177.45,
        "duration": 4.85
    },
    {
        "text": "Tell you, ‘You play good’.",
        "start": 182.3,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "But this is incorrect.",
        "start": 183.42,
        "duration": 2.85
    },
    {
        "text": "Why?",
        "start": 186.27,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "Remember what we said,\n‘good’ is an adjective.",
        "start": 187.64,
        "duration": 3.94
    },
    {
        "text": "It describes a noun.",
        "start": 191.59,
        "duration": 2.42
    },
    {
        "text": "Do you see a noun in that sentence?",
        "start": 194.01,
        "duration": 2.71
    },
    {
        "text": "I don't.",
        "start": 196.72,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "But we have a verb, ‘you play’,\nso what you need is not an adjective,",
        "start": 198.01,
        "duration": 5.78
    },
    {
        "text": "it's an adverb.",
        "start": 203.79,
        "duration": 1.12
    },
    {
        "text": "‘You play well’.",
        "start": 204.91,
        "duration": 3.85
    },
    {
        "text": "If you say,\n‘You speak English good’,",
        "start": 208.76,
        "duration": 4.44
    },
    {
        "text": "again incorrect.",
        "start": 213.2,
        "duration": 3.02
    },
    {
        "text": "Because you need to describe the verb ‘speak’.",
        "start": 216.22,
        "duration": 4.02
    },
    {
        "text": "So you need an adverb.",
        "start": 220.24,
        "duration": 1.33
    },
    {
        "text": "‘You speak English well’.",
        "start": 221.57,
        "duration": 2.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay?",
        "start": 224.52,
        "duration": 1.32
    },
    {
        "text": "So it's very important for you\nto know the difference between adjectives",
        "start": 225.84,
        "duration": 5.24
    },
    {
        "text": "and adverbs.",
        "start": 231.08,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "Especially in this case, with ‘good’ as\nan adjective",
        "start": 232.43,
        "duration": 4.029
    },
    {
        "text": "and ‘well’ as an adverb’.",
        "start": 236.46,
        "duration": 2.88
    },
    {
        "text": "So please try to remember these rules.",
        "start": 239.34,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "Try to use it properly and speak good English.",
        "start": 242.88,
        "duration": 3.96
    },
    {
        "text": "Thank you guys for watching my video.",
        "start": 249.64,
        "duration": 1.6
    },
    {
        "text": "I hope you've liked it.",
        "start": 251.25,
        "duration": 2.16
    },
    {
